Date: 15 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 15 Apr 2003
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 3 PM 15 Apr 2003, an additional 42 patients were confirmed to have
atypical pneumonia following previous admission to public hospitals. They
include 11 healthcare workers (3 from Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole
Hospital, 3 from Prince of Wales Hospital, 2 from Kwong Wah Hospital, 2
from Princess Margaret Hospital, and one from Queen Elizabeth Hospital).
The remaining 31 were other patients and contacts of patients with atypical
pneumonia.
A total of 243 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 14 were discharged
today. 127 patients are receiving treatment in intensive care units.
9 patients died in Queen Elizabeth Hospital, United Christian Hospital,
Princess Margaret Hospital, and Prince of Wales Hospital. This brought to
56 the total number of deaths relating to atypical pneumonia. The deceased
include 4 men and one woman, aged from 45 to 84, who have a history of
chronic diseases. The remaining are a 45-year-old man and 3 women, aged 32,
34, and 37. [according to a table in an annex at the above website link,
these latter 4 deaths were in individuals without a history of chronic
disease. - Mod.MPP]
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Cumulative no. cases/ no. discharged cases/ no. deaths
Health care workers of Hospitals/Clinics and medical students: 291/ 95/ 56
Patients, family members & visitors: 941/ 148/ 0
Total: 1232/ 243/ 56
