[3]
Date: 15 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Singapore - Ministry of Health [edited]
<http://app.moh.gov.sg/sar/sar0301.asp?id=1&mid=6160>

SARS Situation Update 15 Apr 2003
As at 15 Apr 2003, 1 additional SAR patient has been discharged, bringing
the total number of patients who have recovered from SARS to 85. 64 SARS
patients remain hospitalised.
There are 4 additional SARS cases reported today, all linked to the
Singapore General Hospital (SGH) cluster. These are patients who had been
earlier admitted to Tan Tock Seng Hospital (TTSH) as suspect cases and who
have now been diagnosed as having SARS, as they have developed signs of
lung infection on chest-X-ray. They include 1 SGH staff member, 1
inpatient, and 2 visitors. A SARS patient in intensive care died today. He
was a relative of one of the 3 initial index cases.
Information on additional probable cases
So far, 62 persons are linked to the SGH cluster, comprising 41 probable
and 21 suspect SARS cases. They consist of 26 SGH staff, 16 inpatients, and
20 visitors. They are all currently warded in TTSH.
Summary of SARS cases
Below is the summary of the SARS cases to date:
Discharged: 85
Hospitalised: 64 (including 18 in intensive care)
Deaths: 11 + 2 (pending post mortem findings)
Total: 162
Suspected: 86 (including 7 children below 18)
Under home quarantine orders: 575
